Vcs-Git: git://github.com/jollyroger/s3fs-fuse.git -b debian

Package: s3fs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, fuse, mime-support
Description: FUSE-based file system backed by Amazon S3
 s3fs is a FUSE filesystem that allows you to mount an Amazon S3 bucket
 as a local filesystem.  It stores files natively and transparently in
 S3 (i.e., you can use other programs to access the same files).
 Maximum file size=64GB (limited by s3fs, not Amazon).
 .
 s3fs is stable and is being used in number of production environments,
 e.g., rsync backup to s3.

Package: s3fs-dbg
Section: debug
Architecture: any
Priority: extra
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, s3fs ( = ${binary:Version})
Description: FUSE-based file system backed by Amazon S3 (debugging symbols)
 s3fs is a FUSE filesystem that allows you to mount an Amazon S3 bucket
 as a local filesystem.  It stores files natively and transparently in
 S3 (i.e., you can use other programs to access the same files).
 Maximum file size=64GB (limited by s3fs, not Amazon).
 .
 s3fs is stable and is being used in number of production environments,
 e.g., rsync backup to s3.
 .
 This package contains debugging symbols.
 Please install it to create meaningful backtraces when reporting bugs.
